        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 23 at 11:05AM EDT until August 26 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Waves 2 to 4 feet today building to 3 to 5 feet on Sunday
through Tuesday. High wave action, strong currents, and
dangerous swimming conditions expected. Piers will be heavily
swamped by waves.

* WHERE...In Indiana, Northern La Porte county. In Michigan,
Northern Berrien and Southern Berrien counties.

* WHEN...Through Tuesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers. Wear a life vest when on or around
the water.</instruction>
